# LoreLake Install Plan — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> Generated: {{DATE}}
> Plugin install: {{PLUGIN_PATH}}
> Project root: {{PROJECT_ROOT}}

This plan installs LoreLake into `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/`. Execute it once. It is idempotent — re-running is safe and skips already-completed steps. On interrupt, resume by re-running and logging into `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/log.md`.

Each phase appends a completion entry to `log.md`. Resumption: read the log tail; continue from the next unfinished phase.

---

## Phase 1 — Create LoreLake structure

- [ ] Create directory `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/`
- [ ] Write `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/config.json` with the embedded config (see "Embedded config" section at the bottom of this file)
- [ ] Create empty subdirs: `wiki/`, `wiki/discussions/`, `wiki/decisions/`, `wiki/gotchas/`, `wiki/playbook/`, `.state/`, `.state/agents/`, `.state/sessions/`
- [ ] Create stub category index files:
  - `wiki/discussions/discussions.md` with frontmatter and a placeholder "no entries yet"
  - `wiki/decisions/decisions.md` (same)
  - `wiki/gotchas/gotchas.md` (same)
  - `wiki/playbook/playbook.md` (same)
- [ ] Create `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/index.md` from `{{PLUGIN_PATH}}/templates/index.md.tmpl` with substitutions: `PROJECT_NAME={{PROJECT_NAME}}`, `DATE={{DATE}}`
- [ ] Create empty `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/log.md` (will be appended throughout this plan)
- [ ] Create `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/last-ingest-sha`:
  - If git repo: write `git -C {{PROJECT_ROOT}} rev-parse HEAD`
  - If not git: write empty file
- [ ] **Append to `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/llake/log.md`:**
  ```
  ## [{{DATE}}] install-plan | Phase 1 complete: structure created
  ```

## Phase 2 — Update .gitignore

- [ ] Read `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}/.gitignore` (create if missing)
